  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The safety requirement governing this use case mandates that predicted hemolysis indices remain below the clinical threshold (RH < 1) and, critically, that impeller tip speed must not exceed 8.5 m/s under any evaluated operating condition to prevent sub-lethal erythrocyte damage at shear rates above 500 Pa. This tip-speed constraint is treated as a binding safety obligation for the credibility package.",
